## Phase 3: Interactive Clarification

Now clarify the requirements through structured questions. Ask these in order.

### Question 1: Problem Statement

Use AskUserQuestion:

> Let me make sure I understand the problem:
>
> [Restate what you understand from the user's input]
>
> **Is this correct? What's missing or wrong?**

Let the user confirm or correct. If input was minimal, ask:

> Help me understand what you want to build:
>
> A) I'll describe it in my own words
> B) I have a UI mockup/screenshot to share
> C) I want something similar to [existing feature]
> D) Let me share my screen/walk you through it

### Question 2: Target Users

Use AskUserQuestion:

> Who will use this feature?
>
> A) End users (customers)
> B) Internal users (team members)
> C) API consumers (other systems)
> D) Administrators
>
> **Describe the primary user persona.**

### Question 3: Core Functionality

Use AskUserQuestion:

> Based on your description, I understand the core functions are:
>
> 1. [Function 1]
> 2. [Function 2]
> 3. [Function 3]
>
> **What's missing? What's the priority order?**

Options:
- A) This looks right вҖ” continue
- B) I need to add more functions
- C) I need to change the priorities
- D) Let me explain differently

### Question 4: Constraints & Requirements

Use AskUserQuestion:

> Any constraints I should know about?
>
> **Select all that apply:**
> - Performance requirements (response time < X ms)
> - Security requirements (auth, encryption, audit)
> - Compatibility requirements (browsers, devices, APIs)
> - Timeline constraints (need by date X)
> - Budget constraints
> - Integration requirements (must work with X)

### Question 5: Success Criteria

Use AskUserQuestion:

> How will you know this is done right?
>
> **What are the acceptance criteria?**
>
> Example format:
> - Given [context], when [action], then [result]
> - User can [do X] within [Y seconds]
> - System handles [Z concurrent users]

Let user provide specific, testable criteria.

